title: Safety Induction
description: Create awareness of safety culture at your work place

components.html: Welcome to our Warehouse Safety Training Module. Safety is our top priority, and this training is designed to ensure that every member of our team understands the importance of maintaining a safe working environment. Warehouses can be busy and dynamic places, with numerous potential hazards. Through this training, you will learn the essential principles and best practices that will help protect you, your colleagues, and our valuable inventory. Whether you're a seasoned warehouse professional or just starting your career in this field, this module is your key to fostering a culture of safety, preventing accidents, and promoting a healthy and productive work environment. Let's get started on the journey to becoming safety-conscious warehouse professionals.
components.label: Content
Content

components.html: Do you know the basics of warehouse safety? Test your knowledge and see how your perceptions stack up against the experts. Use this as a learning tool to improve your safety performance on the job!
components.label: Content

questions.label: 1. You should drive forklifts backwards down a decline if possible to reduce the chances of a load slipping and falling
2. As long as you are careful, it is okay to stand between a dock and a trailer
3. Cuts, bruises, pinch-point injuries, scalds and burns are all injuries you could receive from a conveyor belt
4. Warehousing is a dangerous industry because the large amount of bulk material being stored could easily ignite
5. The best ergonomic practice for warehouses is to lift items only when necessary
6. If the personal protective equipment (PPE) your employer provides for you is uncomfortable, it is OK not to wear it
7. Smoking and horseplay are allowed in the warehouse if they are done in an open area away from materials, debris and clutter
8. When handling materials, you should always place heavier loads on lower or middle shelves

components.label: Score
components.calculateValue:
const answers = {
  question1: "true",
  question2: "false",
  question3: "true",
  question4: "true",
  question5: "true",
  question6: "false",
  question7: "flase",
  question8: "true",
}

let score = 0
_.forEach(data.quiz, (value, key) => {
  const correct = answers[key] === value
  if(correct)
    score = score + 1
})

value = score
